bug.short_desc: System hangs on Java memory allocation
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1190773 journalctl -k -b -1
Description of problem:
When building my project in Android studio at some point the system will hang, exactly like this:
https://lkml.org/lkml/2016/6/23/210
The system does not recover, this is a hard crash.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
Since kernel 4.6.+ it does not happen on kernel 4.5.+
How reproducible:
Every couple of hours working with ItelliJ (Android Studio and a couple of projects open and building)
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Open Android studio 2. work. 3. system hangs after a few builds.
Actual results:
Expected results:
System should not hang, maybe kill the guilty process or whatever it used to do before.
Additional info:
This is stable Fedora 25 and has been happening since kernel 4.6.+ upgrades.
If it helps, this is a Dell XPS 13 developer edition with an Intel i5 and 8GB of RAM

Update:
I have not experienced this problem with 4.6.7-300.fc24.x86_64 perhaps this is fixed now.
Thanks, closing, feel free to reopen if it pops back up.
